definition.value: A galactosyl group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactose.
A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is hexadecane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1.
An amino disaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine having a 4-deoxy-alpha-L-threo-hex-4-enopyranuronosyl residue attached at the 3-position.
